{"title":"Ritchey Comp Buzzard Handlebar","link":"https://theradavist.com/ritchey-comp-buzzard-handlebar/","date":1709736864000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2133\" height=\"1422\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?fit=1200,1422&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?w=2133&amp;quality=75 2133w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Ritchey-Comp-Buzzard.jpeg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>As one of the innovators of mountain bike handlebars, Ritchey knows a thing or two about designing them for modern riders. Let’s take a look at the new Comp Buzzard ($49.95) below…<span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"5341\" height=\"3561\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?fit=1200,3561&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?w=5341&amp;quality=75 5341w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/RitcheyCompBuzzardWhite.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Ritchey’s new handlebar, the Comp Buzzard offers 820 mm of width 70 mm flat rise, a modest reach, and 27.5° backsweep. This ergonomic combination promotes a more upright and comfortable riding position, relieves pressure from the wrists, and allows the rider to settle back and into the bike – rather than hunching over in an aggressive and non-sustainable angle.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Material: double-butted 6061 alloy</li>\n<li>Width: 820 mm</li>\n<li>Rise: 70 mm flat rise</li>\n<li>Backsweep: 27.5°</li>\n<li>Clamp diameter: 31.8mm</li>\n<li>Bar-end compatible: yes</li>\n<li>Weight: 367g</li>\n<li>Color: BB black</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/bike/handlebars/comp-buzzard-handlebar\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/ritchey-comp-buzzard-handlebar/\">Ritchey Comp Buzzard Handlebar</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"8ffe5527d9045d2510c5d522d56c4612c72239b25718061d0f83f6ee02d6a409","category":"Cycling"}